      "name": "Sidebar-Final-Demo",
      "context": "this bar is really long now so we need to enable overflow vertical scroll and shorten it, look at the existing logic of the sidenav panel, it should fill the view port of the screen essentially. so we should decide what should always be in here and which parts should be overflow scrollable. I think the top layer (sidebar-header), \"search-row\" should be stuck up top, in the bottom the sidebar-footer should be stuck, the rest should be scrollable and have overflow content.\n\nAll icons need to be changed for carbon icons. \n\nMany sizes arent good either and we need to find a smart system. Also dont just recreate all these hardcoded things!! we need to build sub components to use in the sidepanel. like the clickable expandable items, we need to figure out a SMART and intricate way of sub components and a component system. like teh \"buttons\" clickable thing with the chevron. we need to create an intricate ssytem for all of this, preferably one component with like tons of different variants, sizes, forms etc (some with chevron, some without etc). \n\nFor that system we need to figure out good heights, like 20px 24px 28px 32px 36px etc, now many heights of the clickable expandable items are jsut set to hug. better having fixed height and width set to fill the parents.\n\nShould be 280px to match the current side panel size.",
